    {
      "id": "CVE-2026-41156",
      "publishedDate": "2026-06-19T09:28:53.868Z",
      "lastModifiedDate": "2026-06-19T09:28:53.868Z",
      "description": "Software installed and run as a non-privileged user may conduct improper GPU system calls to cause mismanagement of resources creating a write use after free scenario.\n\n\n\nA shared resource (memory page) managed by a CPU thread of control (driver) and accessed by a GPU thread of control (Firmware) can cause a write UAF when the CPU thread frees the resource before the GPU FW has finished accessing it.",
      "severity": "N/A",
